Connection con is used for connecting to MySQL server and for executing queries. 
Statement is for prepared statements.
String variables, where user data is temporarily stored. Same with the arrays below it.

Now, for the connectToDB() method.. 
[code]
public void connectToDB() {
		con = null;
		try {
			Class.forName("com.mysql.jdbc.Driver").newInstance();
			con = DriverManager.getConnection("jdbc:mysql://"+host+"/"+database, username, password);
			if(!con.isClosed()) {
				System.out.println("Connected to MySQL.");
			}
		} catch(Exception e) {
			System.err.println("Exception: " + e.getMessage());
		}
	}
[/code]
Looking over the code you'll notice it loads the driver and starts it, then uses the Connection con to connect to MySQL.
The catch is if there is an error (connection refused, invalid password, can't connect, whatever else may happen..).

